        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1288779225" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11636896977826438963"><a href='https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=FNuOFw1ecJE' rel='nofollow noopener'>Click here</a> to watch a video featuring this book on my channel, <i>From Beginning to Bookend</i>.<br/><br/>Cataloged as historical fiction, this book divulges the story of several immigrants living in New York at the turn-of-the-century, but the author subtly weaves two unique immigrant characters into the narrative, a golem and a jinni, giving the book an element of fantasy. Maybe it was the jinni&apos;s mysterious origin story unfolding, or the golem&apos;s emotional plight, or perhaps it was just fun to look through a p</span>
  <span id="freeText11636896977826438963" style="display:none"><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=FNuOFw1ecJE" rel="nofollow noopener">Click here</a> to watch a video featuring this book on my channel, <i>From Beginning to Bookend</i>.<br /><br />Cataloged as historical fiction, this book divulges the story of several immigrants living in New York at the turn-of-the-century, but the author subtly weaves two unique immigrant characters into the narrative, a golem and a jinni, giving the book an element of fantasy. Maybe it was the jinni's mysterious origin story unfolding, or the golem's emotional plight, or perhaps it was just fun to look through a picture window and see what life was like for those who crossed the ocean and smiled with tears in their eyes when they saw a crowned woman holding a torch to the sky; whatever the reason, its temperate pace was not enough to stop me from turning page after page after page.</span>
